review:
Great just like the two previous games. Matt Bozon & co. simply know what they're doing and that's that.

[b]Pros[/b]:
- Quality action/adventure in the vein of Metroid (in a cartoonish 1001 Nights-inspired setting);
- Tight controls;
- Nice difficulty curve (difficulty is only average, but the ramping up difficulty felt properly satisfying to me);
- Great art and character animations, as is always the case with WayForward;
- [url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=n4LrEWXuZRI]Great soundtrack[/url] by Jake Kaufman (other Shantae games, Mighty Switch Force, Shovel Knight);
- Lots of variety in every aspect, from enemies to levels to music to gameplay mechanics.

[b]Cons[/b]:
- Initially feels a bit limited, takes a bit of time to [i]really[/i] get going (although never to the point of boredom for me personally);
- Some people might not like old-school backtracking (e.g. you get an item--now you must find which previously met NPC to show it to);
- Wacky writing occasionally feels a bit dumb rather than silly, but that's rare and mostly in the beginning;
- High-res character portraits and fonts clash awfully and quite inexcusably with pixel-painted graphics;
- Post-game / good ending stuff can get a tad tiresome, although the true final boss is satisfying enough.

[b]All in all[/b]: despite the stuff listed as flaws, it's one of the best games in the action/adventure ("metroidvania") genre. Get this game and play it, you people. WayForward is a great studio. God bless WayForward. Also, hope you like breasts, hips and innuendo, because that's how they roll.

Review in portuguese and english languages:

[b]Análise em Português:[/b]
Para quem é fã da série clássica de Castlevania (plataforma 2D) deve experimentar esse jogo.

[u]Os pontos positivos são:[/u]
+ A protagonista é uma dançarina da dança-do-ventre, então cuidados com as screenshots;
+ História, no todo;
+ A trilha sonora é muito boa;
+ Jogabilidade suave e fluida;
+ Os gráficos, mesmo em 2D, são muito bons e não são poluídos;
+ Dificuldade muito boa;
+ Diálogos engraçados;
+ Ótima sequência.  E você nem precisa jogar o anterior pra entender muito da história;
+ Boa quantidade de conquistas Steam, sendo algumas um tanto quanto desafiadoras;

[u]Os contras são:[/u]
- Os gráficos poderiam ter sido um pouco mais polidos, nada que atrapalhe;
- Algumas habilidades que você compra durante o jogos são um tanto quanto inúteis;

De maneira geral, ótimo jogo é ótimo e vale a pena ter na biblioteca.
[u]Numa escala de pontuação:[/u] [b]9/10[/b]. [i]Extremamente recomendado.[/i]

[b]English review:[/b]
For those people that are fan of the classic Castlevania (2D platform) you should try out this game.

[u]The pros:[/u]
+ The protagonist is a belly dancer, so beware the screenshooting all the time;
+ The game story and the overall plot;
+ Soundtrack is very good;
+ The artwork, even though it’s 2D, it’s good and not polluted;
+ Good challenging;
+ Great sequel. You don’t even have to play the previous games to understand the history;
+ Nice quantity of Steam achievements, being some of them a bit challenging;

[u]The cons:[/u]
- The graphics could be more polished;
- Some battle skills you can buy during game are pretty much useless;

Overall, this is a very good game and it’s worth having on your Steam account.
[u]In a ranking scale:[/u]  [b]9/10[/b]. [i]Extremely recommended.[/i]
